<nowiki>{{Infobox</nowiki>{{Infobox ancient site| name = Kabutozuka Kofun| image =File:Kabutozuka-kofun 2005-07.jpg| Caption = July 2005| location = {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県}}{{ill|Sendai|ja|仙台市}}{{ill|Taihaku Ward|ja|太白区}}, Negishimachi 14| Latitude degrees = 38 | Latitude minutes = 14 | Latitude seconds = 19.2 | N/S = N | Longitude degrees = 140 | Longitude minutes = 53 | Longitude seconds = 3.2 | E/W = E| Map country code = JP| Shape = {{ill|Keyhole-shaped tumulus|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun}}| Construction era = Late {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀}}| Burial facility =| Scale = Approx. 75 {{ill|meters|ja|メートル}} long| Buried individual =| Excavated artifacts =| Historic site designation =| Notes =}}'''Kabutozuka Kofun''' (兜塚古墳) is a {{ill|tumulus|ja|古墳}} located on the grounds of the present-day {{ill|Miyagi Prefectural Sendai Minami High School|ja|宮城県仙台南高等学校}} in {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県}}, {{ill|Sendai|ja|仙台市}}, {{ill|Taihaku Ward|ja|太白区}}. It is a scallop-shaped {{ill|keyhole-shaped tumulus|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun}} estimated to have been constructed in the late {{ill|5th century|ja|5世紀}}. Measuring approximately 75 {{ill|meters|ja|メートル}} in total length, it features {{ill|fukiishi|ja|葺石}} and {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪}}, making it one of the largest tumuli in the Sendai Plain during its era.

